thread.title: EuroMillions results live: Tuesday's winning National Lottery numbers for a £32m jackpot - Devon Live

title: EuroMillions results live: Tuesday's winning National Lottery numbers for a £32m jackpot - Devon Live
text:
Euromillions numbers (Image: Johnny Green/PA Wire)
Tonight's Euromillions jackpot prize is an eye-watering £32 million.
Should you want to splash it on luxury holidays and homes or pay off a mortgage, debts and bills - it's an incredible sum of money.
EuroMillions draws take place on Tuesday and Friday evenings from approximately 8.30pm.
And one lucky ticket-holder could be scooping the eye-watering sum if their numbers are right - could it be you?
Scroll down for the results in our live blog
Players of EuroMillions are also given an automatic entry into the UK Millionaire Maker - where they must match with a drawn code. EuroMillions draw
A EuroMillions ticket costs £2.50 and players must select five numbers from 1-50 and two lucky star numbers from 1-12.
Fancy boosting you chances? Players can play up to seven lines of numbers on each pay slip and buy 10 slips at a time. Read More Brexit is good news for Euromillions Lottery players but only if you win the jackpot
You can play up to four weeks in advance and ticket sales close at 7:30pm - around an hour before EuroMillions draw on Tuesdays and Fridays.
Check back here later for the full set of EuroMillions results, as well as Millionaire Maker codes, in our live coverage of the draw below. More On
